in powershell, use this command for sudo like behavior
    Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser

command to run babel and watch
    babel ./src/app.js --out-file=./public/scripts/app.js --presets="env,react" --watch


git
  initialise the project - go to root folder 
  > git init
  check status of files
  > git status
  to ignore certain files and directories, add them in .gitignore file
  add files to staging area
  > git add 'file.js'
  to add all files in current directory
  > git add .
  to commit files from staging
  > git commit -m "message"